# UI loading state — client data fetch

Use the shared **`LoadingState`** component whenever a feature shows a loading
UI **after initial page paint** while client data is in flight (TanStack Query
`isPending`, empty cache refetch, filter/page changes with no rows yet).

Route-level navigation loading stays in **`PageLoadingOverlay`** /
`(authenticated)/loading.tsx`. Do not reuse `LoadingState` for that.

## Component

Location: `src/components/shared/LoadingState/`

```tsx
import { LoadingState } from "@/components/shared/LoadingState";

{query.isPending ? (
  <LoadingState resourceName="users" />
) : (
  /* content */
)}
```

### Props

| Prop | Required | Purpose |
|------|----------|---------|
| `resourceName` | yes | Sentence-case fragment appended to `"Loading …"` |
| `className` | no | Override layout for tight containers (dropdowns, table cells) |

Message format is built by `formatLoadingMessage()` in
`LoadingState/constants.ts`:

```ts
formatLoadingMessage("users"); // → "Loading users…"
```

- **Sentence case** for the resource fragment (`users`, `your profile`, `audit logs`).
- **Unicode ellipsis** (`…`), not three ASCII periods.
- Do **not** store per-feature `LOADING_BODY` / `LIST_LOADING_BODY` strings.
  Pass `resourceName` at the call site instead.

### Layout

`LoadingState` centers a **spinner + message** inside its parent (card content,
section, table cell). The parent supplies bounds; do not wrap with extra
loading-specific layout unless a compact override is needed.

Compact override example (notification dropdown):

```tsx
<LoadingState resourceName="notifications" className="min-h-0 py-4" />
```

## DataTable

Pass **`loadingResourceName`** alongside `loading`:

```tsx
<DataTable
  loading={loading}
  loadingResourceName="users"
  /* … */
/>
```

Do not render custom loading text inside table cells. `DataTable` delegates to
`LoadingState`.

## When not to use

| Case | Use instead |
|------|-------------|
| Client route navigation (link click) | `PageLoadingOverlay` via navigation loading host |
| SSR route segment streaming | `(authenticated)/loading.tsx` |
| Mutation / submit in progress | Button label in feature `constants.ts` (`Saving…`, `Sending…`) |
| Action-specific multi-step copy | Feature-local copy (e.g. invite accept checking vs accepting) |
| Inline row refresh while rows exist | Keep showing rows; disable toolbar via `fetching` |

## Anti-patterns

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — plain text, no spinner, duplicated copy constant
export const LOADING_BODY = "Loading users…";
<p className={LOADING_TEXT_CLASS}>{LOADING_BODY}</p>

// ❌ BAD — ad-hoc spinner + message
<div className="flex items-center gap-2">
  <Spinner />
  <span>Loading communities...</span>
</div>

// ✅ GOOD
<LoadingState resourceName="users" />
```

## Accessibility

`LoadingState` renders `role="status"`, `aria-live="polite"`, and
`aria-label` from the formatted message. Do not nest a second status region
around it.

When adding or touching loading UI, migrate nearby violations in the same
feature folder when reasonable.
